# Data Protection Policy

Last Updated: [DATE]

## 1. Purpose

This Data Protection Policy outlines our commitment to protecting personal data processed through our GitHub repository and related services.

## 2. Scope

This policy applies to all contributors, users, and maintainers of [Your Project Name].

## 3. Data Protection Principles

We adhere to the following principles:
- Lawfulness, fairness, and transparency
- Purpose limitation
- Data minimization
- Accuracy
- Storage limitation
- Integrity and confidentiality
- Accountability

## 4. Roles and Responsibilities

### 4.1 Maintainers
- Implement appropriate technical and organizational measures
- Ensure compliance with data protection laws
- Respond to data subject requests

### 4.2 Contributors
- Only process personal data when necessary
- Follow security best practices
- Report any data breaches immediately

## 5. Security Measures

We implement measures including:
- Access controls to the repository
- Regular security reviews
- Secure development practices
- Encryption where appropriate

## 6. International Data Transfers

As GitHub operates globally, data may be transferred internationally. We rely on GitHub's compliance with applicable data transfer mechanisms.

## 7. Breach Notification

In case of a data breach, we will:
- Assess the risk to individuals
- Notify affected parties when required
- Report to authorities if necessary

## 8. Compliance

We aim to comply with:
- General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
- California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
- Other applicable data protection laws
